honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl

Class Miscellaneous_DPL

  • java.lang.Object
    • honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl.PrinterData_DPL
      • honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl.PrinterState_DPL
        • honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl.Miscellaneous_DPL
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class Miscellaneous_DPL
extends PrinterState_DPL
    This class handles the miscellaneous data from the [STX]KcQQQ query as well as accessors to read the data values.

    This class supports the following possible parameters:

    ParameterDescription
    DRDelay Rate
    PSPresent Sensor Equipped
    CECutter Equipped
    CCControl code
    EQStart of Print Signal
    EPEnd of Print Signal
    GSGPIO Slew
    FMFeedback Mode Enable
    CHCommunication Heat Commands Enable
    CSCommunication Speed Commands Enable
    CTCommunication TOF Commands Enable
    BPBritish Pound Enable
    BLGPIO Backup Label
    SVSoftware Switch
    SMMaximum Length Ignore Enable
    PMPause Mode Enable
    PEPeel Mode Enable
    ZCUSB Mode
    WDWindows Driver For EZ_RLE
    DNDisplay Mode for IP Hostname
    HDHex Dump Mode Enable
    ZALCD Orientation
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    • Constructor Detail

      • Miscellaneous_DPL

        public Miscellaneous_DPL(ConnectionBase conn)
        The default constructor will initialize the class with default values.

        Initially all of the _IsValid parameters will be false because no data has been processed. To 'populate' the values, the object must invoke @see PrinterState_DPL.queryPrinter(int) with the query response string.

        Parameters:
        conn - connection to printer
